# ATTENTION: 
# ==========
# This ignore setting requires a new STM32CubeMX code generation 
# and a CMake Rebuild run after each Git clone!
#
# STM32CubeMX:
# ------------
# You can start the code generation manual:  
# - Option 1: VSCode command ">vDevSTM32:Run CubeMX Code Generation"
# - Option 2: open .ioc file in STM32CubeMX tool, click button "GENERATE CODE"
#
# CMake:
# ------
# To rebuild the code from scratch use the following two VSCode commands:
# 1. Reconfig CMake build environment: ">CMake:Delete Cache and Reconfigure"
# 2. Clean and Rebuild complete project: ">CMake:Clean Rebuild"


# Ignore all generated stuff:
# ===========================
#
# Generated by STM32CubeMX tool (GUI/CLI):
# ----------------------------------------
#
# FOLDERS:
cmake/
Core/
Drivers/
Middlewares/
AZURE_RTOS/
#
# FILES:
mx.scratch
/.mxproject
/CMakePresets.json
/startup_stm32*xx.s
/STM32*XX_FLASH.ld
#
# Generated by STM32CubeMX for VS Code extension:
# ----------------------------------------
# FILES:
.clangd
/.settings/bundles-lock.store.json
/.vscode/c_cpp_properties.json
/.vscode/settings.json
#
# Generated by CMake:
# ----------------------------------------
# FOLDERS:
build/ 


# Revert the ignore for special files:
# ====================================
#
# Revert a possible ignore for /CMakeLists.txt files:
#   The /CMakeLists.txt file in root is normaly generated by STMCubeMX but we have
#   added the call of our /Application/CMakeLists.txt at the end of file.
#   This revert is only paranoia, because the root folder is normaly not ignored.
!/CMakeLists.txt
#
# Revert ignore for special files in /Core/Src files:
#   Some files we have changed here. Therefore we ignore first the complete folder 
#   and now we revert this ignore for only this changed files.
!/Core/Src/main.c         # Added: Call of Setup() and Loop() function.
!/Core/Src/stm32*xx_it.c  # Added: debug code in HardFault_Handler() function.
!/Core/Src/usart.c        # Added: debug function int __io_putchar().
